						<summary>

						<p>Pillar in the <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> on the south side of the Vishnu temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Pramādi, Vaiśākha śu. 15.</hi> Since the inscription may be assigned to the 18th century, on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>It states the construction of a stone <hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> of 20 <hi rend="italic">ankaṇas,</hi> dedicated to the god Chennakēśavasvāmi by Koṁḍaya, son of Bālaya and grandson of Mēḍā Rudrapa.</p>						

						</summary>
